(2) This Order shall not apply to—
(a) an employee in the civil service;
(b) an employee of a local authority;
(c) a domestic worker;
(d) an employee in an occupation where wages and conditions
of employment are governed by any agreement between
an employer and employee providing for conditions which
are not less favourable to the employee than the minimum
conditions set out in this Order;
(e) an employee in management;
(f) an employee whose conditions of service are more
favourable than the applicable gross pay in this Order;
(g) an employee who is unionised and whose conditions of
service are negotiated through the process of collective
bargaining in accordance with the Industrial and Labour Cap.269
Relations Act; or
(h) in a sector for which the Minister, by statutory instrument,
has prescribed the minimum wage.
Copies of this Statutory Instrument can be obtained from the Government Printer,
P.O. Box 30136, 10101 Lusaka. Price K 12.00 each.
